<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 02 at 6:08PM EDT  by NWS Wilmington</headline>
<description>...INCREASED FIRE DANGER SUNDAY...
In wake of a cold front overnight, drying, accompanied by gusty
NW winds will prevail Sunday, elevating the fire spread potential.
While some areas have had decent rain lately, other parts of SE
NC have received little rainfall over the past several weeks,
and remain vulnerably dry.</description>
<instruction>Please refer to your local burn permitting authorities on whether
you can burn. If you do, you are advised to use extreme caution.</instruction>
